1
00:00:32,166 --> 00:00:34,208
[birds chirping]

2
00:00:40,458 --> 00:00:42,416
[KAWASE] Are you excited
about your first volume

3
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,041
having a release date?

4
00:00:44,125 --> 00:00:47,041
Here's some ideas for the cover.
What are your thoughts?

5
00:00:47,125 --> 00:00:49,208
A lot of your readers
are teenagers and young adults,

6
00:00:49,291 --> 00:00:52,458
so, maybe a bright,
fun design would be good.

7
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:56,375
Then again,
this one is pretty hard-hitting,

8
00:00:56,458 --> 00:00:58,166
and fits the tone
of the story.

9
00:00:58,250 --> 00:00:59,416
Oh, wait,
on second thought,

10
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:01,708
I think this one
is my personal favorite.

11
00:01:01,791 --> 00:01:04,708
Man, it's hard to choose
just one!

12
00:01:04,791 --> 00:01:06,458
Is it, though?

13
00:01:06,541 --> 00:01:10,583
[SUBARU] Most things in life are
pointless to stress out over.

14
00:01:10,666 --> 00:01:14,166
As for me, I just want to live
a quiet life,

15
00:01:14,250 --> 00:01:17,625
and avoid making
any unnecessary waves.

16
00:01:17,708 --> 00:01:20,375
Okay, so, there was one
other marketing-related thing

17
00:01:20,458 --> 00:01:22,958
I wanted to run by you.

18
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:25,916
A book-signing
to commemorate the release.

19
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,333
[gasps]

20
00:01:27,416 --> 00:01:28,916
The sales department
and affiliated bookstores

21
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,416
are really pushing for it.

22
00:01:30,500 --> 00:01:31,875
They think a signing
could boost sales

23
00:01:31,958 --> 00:01:34,333
and create buzz for the release,
so, uh--

24
00:01:34,416 --> 00:01:36,416
-I refuse.
-Huh?

25
00:01:36,500 --> 00:01:38,166
And that's the final word.

26
00:01:40,333 --> 00:01:42,500
[SUBARU] A book signing
is totally out of the question.

27
00:01:42,583 --> 00:01:46,083
I make it a point to avoid
any situation I can't control!

28
00:01:46,166 --> 00:01:49,166
Yeah, to be honest,
I knew even before I asked

29
00:01:49,250 --> 00:01:51,750
that your answer would be
something along those lines.

30
00:01:51,833 --> 00:01:53,375
All right, then.

31
00:01:53,458 --> 00:01:55,708
I'll try to break the news
gently to sales and marketing.

32
00:01:55,791 --> 00:01:58,708
[doorbell rings]

33
00:01:58,791 --> 00:02:01,708
-Are you gonna answer that?
-Probably a solicitor.

34
00:02:01,791 --> 00:02:03,458
-Right, but still...
-[ringing intensifies]

35
00:02:03,541 --> 00:02:05,000
[SUBARU]
They'll go away.

36
00:02:05,083 --> 00:02:08,500
Look, why don't I just politely
send them away for you?

37
00:02:08,583 --> 00:02:10,958
-Huh?
-[ringing continues]

38
00:02:11,041 --> 00:02:13,291
Sure, if you want.

39
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:20,541
[SUBARU] But sometimes, the ones
who can't be controlled...

40
00:02:20,625 --> 00:02:23,041
Hey! What's up, Subaru?

41
00:02:23,125 --> 00:02:24,000
[gasps]

42
00:02:24,083 --> 00:02:26,166
Turned out to be Hiroto!

43
00:02:26,250 --> 00:02:27,875
Can we stay a while?

44
00:02:27,958 --> 00:02:31,000
[SUBARU] Will attack if you
let your guard down!

45
00:04:02,875 --> 00:04:05,375
[SUBARU]
He brought kids?

46
00:04:05,458 --> 00:04:07,291
Go on, you three.

47
00:04:07,375 --> 00:04:09,375
Say hello to Mr. Subaru.

48
00:04:09,458 --> 00:04:10,875
[KIDS]
Okay!

49
00:04:10,958 --> 00:04:12,500
Nice to meet you!

50
00:04:12,583 --> 00:04:15,125
I'm Hayato Yasaka
and I'm in the third grade!

51
00:04:15,208 --> 00:04:18,125
My name's Narumi.
And I'm also in the third grade!

52
00:04:18,208 --> 00:04:19,708
[TWINS giggle]

53
00:04:19,791 --> 00:04:21,583
As you can probably already
tell, these two are twins.

54
00:04:21,666 --> 00:04:22,916
And this cutie...

55
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:26,166
Misora. I'm three!

56
00:04:26,250 --> 00:04:27,583
Very good!

57
00:04:27,666 --> 00:04:30,166
You know how to say
how old you are!

58
00:04:30,250 --> 00:04:31,750
-We know how, too!
-So, um...

59
00:04:31,833 --> 00:04:34,208
Our parents had to
go out of town on short notice.

60
00:04:34,291 --> 00:04:37,125
They'll be gone overnight,
and I got stuck with the runts.

61
00:04:37,208 --> 00:04:39,666
Of course, I had to leave work
early to look after them.

62
00:04:39,750 --> 00:04:42,000
When I mentioned Haru,
they had to meet her.

63
00:04:42,083 --> 00:04:45,541
I'm used to you showing up
unannounced, but this is...

64
00:04:45,625 --> 00:04:48,958
Oh, yeah. You haven't met
the runts before, have you?

65
00:04:50,458 --> 00:04:52,250
[nervously exhales]

66
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:54,875
-[SUBARU] Who's that?
-[HIROTO] Huh?

67
00:04:54,958 --> 00:04:57,625
Oh, that's right.
You met Nagisa, yeah?

68
00:04:57,708 --> 00:04:59,916
But it's been forever.

69
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,083
[YOUNG NAGISA]
Big brother!

70
00:05:02,166 --> 00:05:04,541
♪

71
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,083
[YOUNG NAGISA]
Brother!

72
00:05:10,166 --> 00:05:11,458
[YOUNG SUBARU]
Huh?

73
00:05:11,541 --> 00:05:13,250
[YOUNG HIROTO]
I told you, no girls allowed!

74
00:05:13,333 --> 00:05:14,708
But why?

75
00:05:14,791 --> 00:05:17,666
I wanna come
with you guys, too!

76
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:20,416
-Oh.
-Nice to see you again.

77
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:23,083
Sorry we all just barged in
on you like this.

78
00:05:23,166 --> 00:05:25,250
-Um...
-Where's Haru at?

79
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:26,708
Can we go see her?

80
00:05:26,791 --> 00:05:29,791
Uh, she's around here
somewhere.

81
00:05:29,875 --> 00:05:32,083
[HAYATO]
All right! Operation Find Haru!

82
00:05:32,166 --> 00:05:33,458
[NARUMI, MISORA]
Yeah!

83
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:35,291
Where do you think she's hiding?

84
00:05:35,375 --> 00:05:37,208
[MISORA]
I wanna go pet Haru right now!

85
00:05:37,291 --> 00:05:39,958
Right!
Initiate Operation Find Haru!

86
00:05:40,041 --> 00:05:41,916
[ALL]
Yeah!

87
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:44,500
[SUBARU]
But, Kawase...

88
00:05:44,583 --> 00:05:46,541
[KAWASE moans]

89
00:05:49,041 --> 00:05:51,041
[NARUMI]
Yay! I just saw Haru!

90
00:05:51,125 --> 00:05:53,916
[HAYATO]
She's over there! She ran away!

91
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:57,291
[NARUMI]
Hold on! Aw, she's so cute!

92
00:05:57,375 --> 00:05:59,250
[HIROTO]
Hey, don't. Be gentle with her.

93
00:05:59,333 --> 00:06:01,708
Uh, Kawase...

94
00:06:01,791 --> 00:06:03,166
What is it?

95
00:06:03,250 --> 00:06:04,500
[KAWASE]
I can't stand it!

96
00:06:04,583 --> 00:06:06,166
Those kids get to play
with my sweet Haru,

97
00:06:06,250 --> 00:06:08,041
while I'm stuck in here
adulting with this guy!

98
00:06:08,125 --> 00:06:10,833
Why don't we take
a little break?

99
00:06:10,916 --> 00:06:13,750
[KAWASE]
Okay! Haru-meow!

100
00:06:13,833 --> 00:06:14,916
[sighs]

101
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,250
I guess I'll put
some coffee on.

102
00:06:17,333 --> 00:06:18,958
[gasps]

103
00:06:19,041 --> 00:06:21,000
Oh, Subaru.

104
00:06:21,083 --> 00:06:23,333
Nothing in your fridge
as usual, I see.

105
00:06:23,416 --> 00:06:24,625
[SUBARU]
Didn't your mom teach you

106
00:06:24,708 --> 00:06:26,666
it's rude to raid
other people's fridges?

107
00:06:26,750 --> 00:06:29,416
Yeah, but I'm not.
This is just an inspection.

108
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:31,291
I'm making sure
you're eating right.

109
00:06:31,375 --> 00:06:33,916
[stomach rumbles]

110
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:37,083
I ate... yesterday?
I think.

111
00:06:37,166 --> 00:06:40,791
Dude. You should eat every day.
Jeez.

112
00:06:42,250 --> 00:06:44,708
Ah, takeout, huh?
Listen.

113
00:06:44,791 --> 00:06:46,791
Can I order delivery
from this place?

114
00:06:46,875 --> 00:06:49,791
It'll be on me, of course.
Yeah?

115
00:06:49,875 --> 00:06:51,833
[stomach rumbles]

116
00:06:51,916 --> 00:06:54,083
Sure. I guess.

117
00:06:55,958 --> 00:06:58,708
-Kitty!
-Cuteness overload!

118
00:06:58,791 --> 00:07:00,208
Be gentle, Misora.

119
00:07:00,291 --> 00:07:02,750
-Hurry! I wanna hold Haru next!
-Then it's my turn!

120
00:07:02,833 --> 00:07:05,041
Hey! Misora, over here!

121
00:07:05,125 --> 00:07:07,958
Hey, runts. You guys
feel like some take-out?

122
00:07:08,041 --> 00:07:09,916
We're eating
at Subaru's tonight!

123
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:12,458
-Wow, really?
-Awesome!

124
00:07:12,541 --> 00:07:16,208
Um, Kawase,
you're welcome to join.

125
00:07:16,291 --> 00:07:17,666
Look, "crap" omelet!

126
00:07:17,750 --> 00:07:20,750
[laughing] Crab omelet, huh?
Excellent choice!

127
00:07:20,833 --> 00:07:22,708
Yeah, that's what I want, too!

128
00:07:22,791 --> 00:07:24,375
-[TWINS giggling]
-[SUBARU sighs]

129
00:07:24,458 --> 00:07:26,541
[SUBARU]
I'll have ramen.

130
00:07:26,625 --> 00:07:28,916
Guess I'll go get
everything ready.

131
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,750
Gotcha.

132
00:07:33,333 --> 00:07:35,291
[SUBARU sighs]

133
00:07:35,375 --> 00:07:37,541
[SUBARU]
Give me a friggin' break!

134
00:07:37,625 --> 00:07:39,583
I don't even have
the faintest idea

135
00:07:39,666 --> 00:07:42,000
how I'm supposed
interact with kids!

136
00:07:42,083 --> 00:07:43,416
And I don't think
there have ever been

137
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:45,625
this many people
in this house at once!

138
00:07:45,708 --> 00:07:47,541
Maybe not even total.

139
00:07:47,625 --> 00:07:48,875
Oh, crap!

140
00:07:48,958 --> 00:07:51,833
Do I have enough teacups
for everyone here?

141
00:07:55,125 --> 00:07:56,625
[sighs]

142
00:07:57,750 --> 00:07:59,708
Excuse me.

143
00:08:01,291 --> 00:08:03,250
Do you, um,
need any help in here?

144
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:06,541
-I'm a little bored.
-Huh? Well...

145
00:08:08,458 --> 00:08:10,333
We might need some paper cups.

146
00:08:10,416 --> 00:08:12,333
[SUBARU'S MOM]
Look at this, Subaru!

147
00:08:12,416 --> 00:08:15,333
I found this lovely tea
set on our trip!

148
00:08:15,416 --> 00:08:18,166
It was so beautiful,
I just couldn't resist!

149
00:08:18,250 --> 00:08:19,791
[BOTH chuckle lightly]

150
00:08:19,875 --> 00:08:22,333
Won't it be nice
when we have lots of visitors?

151
00:08:22,416 --> 00:08:24,041
Maybe we can host a party!

152
00:08:24,125 --> 00:08:25,791
Will that ever happen?

153
00:08:25,875 --> 00:08:27,958
Oh, quiet, of course it will!
Please.

154
00:08:28,041 --> 00:08:30,666
I can't wait until
we get to use it together.

155
00:08:30,750 --> 00:08:32,166
[laughs]

156
00:08:33,916 --> 00:08:35,166
[gasps softly]

157
00:08:38,250 --> 00:08:39,875
Found it.

158
00:08:39,958 --> 00:08:42,916
[paper rustling]

159
00:08:45,541 --> 00:08:47,875
Um, I don't think
I've ever known someone

160
00:08:47,958 --> 00:08:49,583
who had as many books as you.

161
00:08:49,666 --> 00:08:52,458
One, two, three, four...

162
00:08:52,541 --> 00:08:54,625
I guess I like to read.

163
00:08:54,708 --> 00:08:56,833
Uh, yeah. So do I.

164
00:08:56,916 --> 00:08:58,916
I'm the student librarian
at my school.

165
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:01,000
It's actually
Reading Week right now.

166
00:09:01,083 --> 00:09:03,125
I'm making a list
of suggested books.

167
00:09:03,208 --> 00:09:06,458
[SUBARU] Wait, maybe barley tea
would be better.

168
00:09:06,541 --> 00:09:08,083
[NAGISA]
Are there any books

169
00:09:08,166 --> 00:09:10,291
you could maybe recommend,
Subaru?

170
00:09:11,541 --> 00:09:14,541
[SUBARU] "Books I'd like
to recommend?"

171
00:09:14,625 --> 00:09:17,125
[YUGO] Actually,
there's a story in here

172
00:09:17,208 --> 00:09:19,291
about a cat you might like.

173
00:09:19,375 --> 00:09:21,291
[SUBARU]
I never imagined I'd be asked

174
00:09:21,375 --> 00:09:23,791
to make a book
recommendation!

175
00:09:23,875 --> 00:09:27,375
There's no way I could narrow
down my favorites to just one!

176
00:09:27,458 --> 00:09:29,708
And I could never explain
what makes each one great

177
00:09:29,791 --> 00:09:31,500
in just a few words!

178
00:09:31,583 --> 00:09:33,208
What do I do?

179
00:09:33,291 --> 00:09:36,958
Besides, she's a girl,
and way younger than me.

180
00:09:37,041 --> 00:09:39,541
I have no idea what kind
of books she'd be into!

181
00:09:39,625 --> 00:09:41,583
How can I make
a good recommendation?

182
00:09:41,666 --> 00:09:43,333
What am I supposed to say?

183
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:45,583
I can't do it!
I'm freaking out!

184
00:09:47,833 --> 00:09:50,083
Sorry. Excuse me.

185
00:09:57,458 --> 00:10:00,875
Was it too soon?
Maybe I was too familiar.

186
00:10:02,458 --> 00:10:04,791
-[SUBARU] Here.
-[NAGISA gasps]

187
00:10:04,875 --> 00:10:08,333
[SUBARU] This book is one
of my all-time favorites.

188
00:10:08,416 --> 00:10:11,375
I was really into it
when I was your age.

189
00:10:13,625 --> 00:10:14,708
[chuckles]

190
00:10:14,791 --> 00:10:17,083
Sure you don't mind
if I borrow it?

191
00:10:17,166 --> 00:10:19,041
Uh, no.

192
00:10:19,125 --> 00:10:21,333
Just bring it back
whenever you're done.

193
00:10:21,416 --> 00:10:23,000
[SUBARU]
Did I do it right?

194
00:10:23,083 --> 00:10:25,541
Is this how you're supposed
to make a recommendation?

195
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:28,500
Thank you!
I can't wait to dive into it!

196
00:10:30,041 --> 00:10:31,750
[SUBARU]
I guess I did.

197
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:35,208
[doorbell rings]

198
00:10:35,291 --> 00:10:37,250
[WOMAN]
Delivery!

199
00:10:37,333 --> 00:10:40,250
[TWINS]
Wow! It looks yummy!

200
00:10:40,333 --> 00:10:43,250
[ALL]
Thank you for the food!

201
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:45,791
Eat food!

202
00:10:48,166 --> 00:10:50,125
Mm! Delicious!

203
00:10:50,208 --> 00:10:52,875
"Crap" omelets are the best!

204
00:10:52,958 --> 00:10:54,500
It's "crab omelet."

205
00:10:54,583 --> 00:10:55,958
[meows]

206
00:10:56,041 --> 00:10:58,041
[ALL laughing]

207
00:11:00,791 --> 00:11:03,458
[HAYATO]
Wow! The ramen looks good, too!

208
00:11:03,541 --> 00:11:05,375
Yeah, it does!

209
00:11:08,458 --> 00:11:10,958
-Uh, you guys wanna try it?
-[BOTH] Yeah!

210
00:11:11,041 --> 00:11:13,250
-I want some, too!
-[meows]

211
00:11:16,125 --> 00:11:18,833
Mm!
This is the best thing ever!

212
00:11:20,166 --> 00:11:21,750
[meowing]

213
00:11:21,833 --> 00:11:23,916
[ALL]
Thanks for the tasty meal!

214
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:26,375
[MISORA]
Yummy!

215
00:11:26,458 --> 00:11:28,500
[sighs]

216
00:11:31,333 --> 00:11:32,916
[SUBARU]
It's finally over.

217
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,416
Peace and quiet at last.

218
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:36,958
[NARUMI] Everybody who wants
to play hide and seek,

219
00:11:37,041 --> 00:11:38,375
touch my finger!

220
00:11:38,458 --> 00:11:40,291
[ALL]
I do!

221
00:11:40,375 --> 00:11:41,375
[SUBARU moans]

222
00:11:41,458 --> 00:11:43,500
[KAWASE]
Everybody hidden?

223
00:11:43,583 --> 00:11:46,708
[KIDS laughing]
You'll never find us!

224
00:11:49,625 --> 00:11:50,458
Oh!

225
00:11:52,708 --> 00:11:53,625
[gasps]

226
00:11:53,708 --> 00:11:55,625
[MISORA]
Shh!

227
00:11:55,708 --> 00:11:57,666
[KAWASE]
Ready or not!

228
00:11:57,750 --> 00:11:59,708
[TWINS]
You'll never find us!

229
00:11:59,791 --> 00:12:01,958
[BOTH]
Shh!

230
00:12:02,041 --> 00:12:04,458
Are you ready?
‘Cause here I come!

231
00:12:04,541 --> 00:12:05,833
[BOTH giggling]

232
00:12:05,916 --> 00:12:07,416
[KAWASE] Now where could
those kids be hiding?

233
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:10,458
Hmm.
Could they be in here?

234
00:12:10,541 --> 00:12:11,916
-[MISORA giggles]
-[KAWASE] Hmm?

235
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,458
What's this, now?

236
00:12:13,541 --> 00:12:17,208
Really? Nobody in here?

237
00:12:17,291 --> 00:12:20,375
Hey, guys! Where did you go?

238
00:12:20,458 --> 00:12:22,333
[TWINS]
Time for a staring contest!

239
00:12:22,416 --> 00:12:25,375
[BOTH exclaiming]

240
00:12:27,666 --> 00:12:29,458
[TWINS exclaiming]

241
00:12:32,375 --> 00:12:34,958
-[BOTH giggling]
-Man, he's good!

242
00:12:35,041 --> 00:12:38,041
Mr. Subaru,
you're a really good starer!

243
00:12:38,125 --> 00:12:41,125
[MISORA laughing]

244
00:12:41,208 --> 00:12:43,500
[HAYATO] Mr. Subaru,
come look at this!

245
00:12:43,583 --> 00:12:45,583
[NARUMI]
Come see how cute Haru is!

246
00:12:45,666 --> 00:12:48,125
[KAWASE]
You are gonna love it!

247
00:12:48,208 --> 00:12:50,625
[GROUP laughing]

248
00:12:50,708 --> 00:12:52,875
[barking]

249
00:12:52,958 --> 00:12:55,125
Oh, what's going on
over there?

250
00:12:55,208 --> 00:12:56,750
Does he have visitors?

251
00:12:56,833 --> 00:12:59,500
Well. Sounds like they're
having a nice time.

252
00:12:59,583 --> 00:13:00,958
-[chuckles]
-[barks]

253
00:13:01,041 --> 00:13:03,541
[HIROTO]
Hayato. Narumi.

254
00:13:03,625 --> 00:13:06,000
Come on,
it's time to go home.

255
00:13:06,083 --> 00:13:08,125
[KAWASE chuckling]
Look at Misora.

256
00:13:08,208 --> 00:13:09,750
She's fast asleep.

257
00:13:09,833 --> 00:13:12,041
Haru must be
hiding somewhere.

258
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:13,916
Yeah, and I wanted
to hold her one last time

259
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,666
before we had to go home.

260
00:13:15,750 --> 00:13:17,750
You held her
enough for one day.

261
00:13:17,833 --> 00:13:20,750
Subaru, thanks
for having us over.

262
00:13:20,833 --> 00:13:22,958
Yeah, thanks for
putting up with us.

263
00:13:24,875 --> 00:13:26,916
I'm exhausted.

264
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:29,416
[TWINS giggling]

265
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:31,916
-Didn't you have fun today?
-[HIROTO laughing]

266
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,458
Next time we come over,
I'll bring you

267
00:13:33,541 --> 00:13:35,166
some of Mom's
cooking to say thanks.

268
00:13:35,250 --> 00:13:37,916
Gotta say, these runts
seem to like you.

269
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:40,458
Let's play again soon,
Mr. Subaru. Okay?

270
00:13:40,541 --> 00:13:43,166
Yeah, next time we'll bring
our friends from class!

271
00:13:44,750 --> 00:13:46,416
[SUBARU]
Ah... Uh-huh.

272
00:13:46,500 --> 00:13:48,791
Well, then, Mikazuki,
see you tomorrow!

273
00:13:48,875 --> 00:13:50,625
[HAYATO]
Aw, no fair!

274
00:13:50,708 --> 00:13:52,833
[NARUMI]
I'm coming over tomorrow, too!

275
00:13:52,916 --> 00:13:53,916
[HIROTO]
Hey, take it easy.

276
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,416
Let's not impose
on Mr. Subaru.

277
00:13:58,791 --> 00:14:00,375
[sighs]

278
00:14:03,708 --> 00:14:06,000
I'll never get
used to people.

279
00:14:06,083 --> 00:14:08,083
[groaning]

280
00:14:18,791 --> 00:14:21,750
Guess you had a pretty
rough day, too, didn't you?

281
00:14:26,333 --> 00:14:27,166
[gasps]

282
00:14:40,458 --> 00:14:42,291
[HARU snoring]

283
00:14:47,041 --> 00:14:49,166
[SUBARU]
She's snoring?

284
00:14:50,791 --> 00:14:54,208
I make it a point to avoid
situations I can't control.

285
00:14:54,291 --> 00:14:57,333
I don't deal well with people
doing things I don't expect.

286
00:14:57,416 --> 00:15:01,875
But, it's only when those
unexpected things happen,

287
00:15:01,958 --> 00:15:04,875
that you make little discoveries
and forge new friendships.

288
00:15:04,958 --> 00:15:07,958
So, every once in a while,

289
00:15:08,041 --> 00:15:10,875
and I mean every once
in a great while...

290
00:15:10,958 --> 00:15:14,208
I guess surprises
might not be so bad.

291
00:15:14,291 --> 00:15:17,791
♪

292
00:15:25,416 --> 00:15:27,166
Maybe I'll give that...

293
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:30,916
a little more thought.

294
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:32,500
[snoring continues]

295
00:15:34,458 --> 00:15:37,000
♪

296
00:15:41,208 --> 00:15:42,541
-[NARUMI] Hey Haru!
-[footsteps running]

297
00:15:42,625 --> 00:15:43,666
Where are you?

298
00:15:43,750 --> 00:15:45,875
[HAYATO]
There you are!

299
00:15:45,958 --> 00:15:47,333
[TWINS giggling]

300
00:15:47,416 --> 00:15:48,875
[HARU]
Wha...

301
00:15:48,958 --> 00:15:50,833
[screams]
What?

302
00:15:50,916 --> 00:15:53,625
What in the world
is happening?

303
00:15:53,708 --> 00:15:55,291
Are enemies attacking?

304
00:15:55,375 --> 00:15:58,166
But this is supposed to be
a safe, quiet place!

305
00:15:58,250 --> 00:16:00,541
-[HARU yelling fearfully]
-[HAYATO] Aw, she ran away!

306
00:16:01,666 --> 00:16:04,583
[HARU] That's right!
Ms. Tora warned me about this.

307
00:16:04,666 --> 00:16:06,916
[TORA] Just be sure you never
let your guard down.

308
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,625
‘Cause a fight
could sneak up on you

309
00:16:08,708 --> 00:16:10,166
when you least expect it.

310
00:16:10,250 --> 00:16:12,916
[HARU] Of course.
I can't just turn tail and run.

311
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:15,375
[hisses]
Bring it on, minions!

312
00:16:15,458 --> 00:16:17,583
Hey, now,
you guys simmer down.

313
00:16:17,666 --> 00:16:18,875
You can play with Haru,

314
00:16:18,958 --> 00:16:20,208
but don't be too loud
or rough with her.

315
00:16:20,291 --> 00:16:21,416
And don't chase her, either.

316
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:23,208
[BOTH]
Fine.

317
00:16:23,291 --> 00:16:25,875
[HARU] Wait! It's that mildly
annoying human.

318
00:16:25,958 --> 00:16:28,333
So, these smaller ones must be
his minions or something.

319
00:16:28,416 --> 00:16:31,041
I definitely can't
let my guard down.

320
00:16:31,125 --> 00:16:34,041
[giggles]
She's got a red bow, too!

321
00:16:34,125 --> 00:16:37,041
[NAGISA] Yes, you're right.
Isn't her ribbon pretty?

322
00:16:37,125 --> 00:16:38,541
-Come over here, Haru.
-Come here, Haru.

323
00:16:38,625 --> 00:16:40,000
[HARU]
What should I do?

324
00:16:40,083 --> 00:16:42,583
Now they've got me
surrounded! Huh?

325
00:16:44,583 --> 00:16:47,541
That big one left.
Now it's just...

326
00:16:47,625 --> 00:16:49,791
these weak-looking
"little ones."

327
00:16:49,875 --> 00:16:52,333
They don't seem
so scary now.

328
00:16:52,416 --> 00:16:53,791
[snickers]

329
00:16:53,875 --> 00:16:55,625
My sheer courage must have
scared the big one off!

330
00:16:55,708 --> 00:16:56,750
-[door thuds]
-[HARU] Huh?

331
00:16:56,833 --> 00:16:58,541
-There she is!
-[HARU] It's him!

332
00:16:58,625 --> 00:17:00,541
When did the super
annoying one get here?

333
00:17:00,625 --> 00:17:03,125
Why do these humans
just keep coming?

334
00:17:04,750 --> 00:17:07,083
Huh?
[yells]

335
00:17:07,166 --> 00:17:08,541
It's all over!

336
00:17:08,625 --> 00:17:10,833
One of them snuck up
behind me!

337
00:17:10,916 --> 00:17:12,791
Guess I'll just have to...

338
00:17:12,875 --> 00:17:14,583
[HARU grunts]

339
00:17:14,666 --> 00:17:16,625
[ALL gasping]

340
00:17:21,375 --> 00:17:22,416
[HARU inhales sharply]

341
00:17:22,500 --> 00:17:24,916
[HARU]
Such a tiny human.

342
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:28,250
[TORA] That means you gotta look
after the runts, all right?

343
00:17:29,791 --> 00:17:32,416
They won't last
long out here otherwise.

344
00:17:35,791 --> 00:17:37,250
Whoa. Crazy.

345
00:17:37,333 --> 00:17:39,666
For a second I was sure
Haru was about to scratch you.

346
00:17:39,750 --> 00:17:41,541
But she's acting really calm.

347
00:17:42,791 --> 00:17:46,000
[HARU] Attacking the weak
and defenseless isn't my style.

348
00:17:46,083 --> 00:17:48,208
Haru is a very sweet kitty!

349
00:17:48,291 --> 00:17:50,916
She doesn't seem bothered
at all by you holding her.

350
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:52,541
I wanna hold Haru, next!

351
00:17:52,625 --> 00:17:54,125
-And then it's my turn!
-[KAWASE chuckles]

352
00:17:54,208 --> 00:17:56,208
Maybe we should let her go
for a bit.

353
00:17:56,291 --> 00:17:58,958
[HARU] They're definitely
invading my personal space,

354
00:17:59,041 --> 00:18:00,708
but they're not
treating me like an enemy.

355
00:18:00,791 --> 00:18:02,041
[HIROTO] Hey!
-[HARU] Huh?

356
00:18:05,041 --> 00:18:07,041
[HARU]
I guess they're done now?

357
00:18:08,541 --> 00:18:12,041
What was that all about?
Humans can be very confusing.

358
00:18:12,125 --> 00:18:15,625
Oh, well, at least now
I can finally relax.

359
00:18:19,666 --> 00:18:20,916
[doorbell ringing]

360
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:22,791
[WOMAN]
Delivery!

361
00:18:24,041 --> 00:18:25,208
[HARU]
Huh?

362
00:18:25,291 --> 00:18:26,791
[HARU]
Hold on. What's this?

363
00:18:28,291 --> 00:18:31,750
[yelling]
I remember... that smell!

364
00:18:31,833 --> 00:18:34,250
Thank you so much
for being patient.

365
00:18:34,333 --> 00:18:37,250
-Hello! It's Haru!
-Hi, Narumi!

366
00:18:37,333 --> 00:18:39,625
Haru, I didn't know
this was your friend's house!

367
00:18:39,708 --> 00:18:41,041
[NARUMI]
No, we don't live here...

368
00:18:41,125 --> 00:18:43,125
[HARU] That's the smell
of the super yummy food

369
00:18:43,208 --> 00:18:44,625
I used to eat!

370
00:18:44,708 --> 00:18:46,083
Huh?

371
00:18:46,166 --> 00:18:48,625
[HARU] That yummy aroma
is making my mouth water!

372
00:18:48,708 --> 00:18:50,291
[GIRL] Hey, Mom, look!
Didn't that kitty

373
00:18:50,375 --> 00:18:51,708
used to come to our house?

374
00:18:51,791 --> 00:18:53,375
[WOMAN] What?
Oh, my goodness,

375
00:18:53,458 --> 00:18:56,125
it's the little cat
who loved my cooking so much!

376
00:18:56,208 --> 00:18:58,375
So, she lives at this house?
Awesome!

377
00:18:58,458 --> 00:19:01,291
[NARUMI] Haru, you mean
you know Haru the cat?

378
00:19:01,375 --> 00:19:03,208
[HAYATO]
And you even have the same name!

379
00:19:03,291 --> 00:19:04,958
Yeah. She used to
come by our house

380
00:19:05,041 --> 00:19:06,791
and eat my mom's food!

381
00:19:06,875 --> 00:19:09,375
But then one day
she just stopped showing up.

382
00:19:09,458 --> 00:19:11,208
I'm so glad to know
she's okay!

383
00:19:11,291 --> 00:19:12,500
How cool!

384
00:19:12,583 --> 00:19:14,375
I've never met a cat
with my name before!

385
00:19:14,458 --> 00:19:18,125
-Well. Time to go now.
-Oh. Okay.

386
00:19:18,208 --> 00:19:19,791
[WOMAN]
Come on, Haru.

387
00:19:19,875 --> 00:19:22,208
[HARU] What? Food? For me?
Can I eat it now?

388
00:19:22,291 --> 00:19:23,666
I'm starving!

389
00:19:23,750 --> 00:19:24,708
-Goodbye!
-[WOMAN chuckling]

390
00:19:24,791 --> 00:19:26,291
See you later, Narumi!

391
00:19:29,083 --> 00:19:31,000
[exclaims happily]

392
00:19:31,083 --> 00:19:34,000
[HARU] I can't believe they
ordered my old favorite for me!

393
00:19:34,083 --> 00:19:36,375
-Gimme! Now!
-[KAWASE] Everybody hidden?

394
00:19:36,458 --> 00:19:37,833
[HARU]
Hey! What's going on?

395
00:19:37,916 --> 00:19:39,958
Let me go.

396
00:19:40,041 --> 00:19:41,833
I don't wanna stay back here.

397
00:19:41,916 --> 00:19:43,791
[TWINS shushing]

398
00:19:43,875 --> 00:19:46,083
A-poo-poo!

399
00:19:46,166 --> 00:19:47,958
[HARU]
Hmm.

400
00:19:50,458 --> 00:19:52,166
Heh. Well, that's
the saddest attempt

401
00:19:52,250 --> 00:19:54,583
at a scary face
I've ever seen.

402
00:19:54,666 --> 00:19:56,458
[MISORA giggles]

403
00:19:56,541 --> 00:19:58,500
Okay, Haru!
You win!

404
00:19:58,583 --> 00:20:00,375
[HARU] Huh?
What is she laughing about?

405
00:20:00,458 --> 00:20:02,333
-What happened?
-[KAWASE] Guys, check it out!

406
00:20:02,416 --> 00:20:03,958
Wanna see Haru play
with this toy?

407
00:20:04,041 --> 00:20:06,000
[KIDS laughing]

408
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:09,458
[HARU]
Huh? What the... ?

409
00:20:09,541 --> 00:20:12,500
I don't know what that is,
but I have to...

410
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:16,958
[yells]

411
00:20:17,041 --> 00:20:19,000
How'd it get away?

412
00:20:19,083 --> 00:20:21,166
[HARU grunting]

413
00:20:22,541 --> 00:20:25,458
[exclaims]

414
00:20:25,541 --> 00:20:26,875
[HARU]
What's happening?

415
00:20:26,958 --> 00:20:28,875
My body!
It's moving against my will!

416
00:20:28,958 --> 00:20:30,208
[ALL]
She's so cute!

417
00:20:30,291 --> 00:20:31,958
[KIDS laughing]

418
00:20:35,791 --> 00:20:36,958
[TARO]
So fun!

419
00:20:37,041 --> 00:20:39,291
I wish I could play
with all of them!

420
00:20:42,291 --> 00:20:45,958
[NARUMI] Yeah, next time we'll
bring our friends from class!

421
00:20:46,041 --> 00:20:47,958
[SUBARU]
Ah... Uh-huh.

422
00:20:48,041 --> 00:20:49,625
[TWINS]
Goodbye!

423
00:20:49,708 --> 00:20:51,791
[door closing]

424
00:20:51,875 --> 00:20:53,291
[HARU sighs]

425
00:20:57,291 --> 00:20:59,333
[sighs]
Finally.

426
00:20:59,416 --> 00:21:01,833
I was scared
they might never leave.

427
00:21:02,875 --> 00:21:04,750
-[body falls]
-Huh?

428
00:21:04,833 --> 00:21:07,250
He's as tired as I am.

429
00:21:07,333 --> 00:21:09,458
Yeah, I guess he would be.

430
00:21:09,541 --> 00:21:10,791
Come on.

431
00:21:10,875 --> 00:21:12,375
You've got
to keep it together, human.

432
00:21:12,458 --> 00:21:13,416
[SUBARU sighs heavily]

433
00:21:13,500 --> 00:21:14,916
[HARU]
Just so we're clear,

434
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:18,041
I had it a lot tougher
than you did today.

435
00:21:18,125 --> 00:21:20,875
Guess you had a pretty
rough day, too, didn't you?

436
00:21:20,958 --> 00:21:21,916
[HARU]
Hmm.

437
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:24,500
Huh?

438
00:21:24,583 --> 00:21:26,583
His smell is nice.

439
00:21:26,666 --> 00:21:29,166
It makes me feel
safe and calm.

440
00:21:29,250 --> 00:21:32,875
[MS. TORA] Just be sure
you never let your guard down.

441
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:36,125
[HARU]
I know that's right, Ms. Tora.

442
00:21:36,208 --> 00:21:40,375
And I understand why.
But still...

443
00:21:42,875 --> 00:21:45,666
Just for right now...

444
00:21:45,750 --> 00:21:47,958
as long as I'm with him,

445
00:21:48,041 --> 00:21:50,250
this is okay, right?

446
00:21:50,333 --> 00:21:53,250
♪

447
00:23:33,125 --> 00:23:35,375
What?
When did they do this?

448
00:23:35,458 --> 00:23:36,833
[gasps]

449
00:23:36,916 --> 00:23:38,416
"Where is the dictionary?"

450
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:41,083
Wait, did they hide it?

451
00:23:41,166 --> 00:23:42,875
Why would they?

452
00:23:42,958 --> 00:23:45,041
Where is it? Little jerks!

453
00:23:47,250 --> 00:23:48,416
[HARU]
Hey, calm down!

454
00:23:48,500 --> 00:23:51,666
The food is right here,
human, see?

455
00:23:51,750 --> 00:23:53,250
[SUBARU]
Where is it?

456
00:23:55,958 --> 00:23:59,000
[TARO] Today was such a fun,
exciting time, don't you think?

457
00:23:59,083 --> 00:24:00,833
[HARU] What?
There was nothing fun about it!

458
00:24:00,916 --> 00:24:02,541
[TARO]
You didn't have a good time?

459
00:24:02,625 --> 00:24:04,541
[HARU] No, I got chased around
by those little minions all day!

460
00:24:04,625 --> 00:24:05,750
[TARO]
Exactly!

